# trivy ignore list for `trivy config` runs over terraform/.
# Each entry is a misconfiguration rule ID; trivy still loads the rule but
# does not fail the run on it. Include a comment for every entry so the
# rationale survives.

# AWS-0104 — Security group rule allows unrestricted egress (0.0.0.0/0).
# Triggered inside the bundled `terraform-aws-modules/eks/.../node_groups.tf`
# (`aws_security_group_rule.node["egress_all"]`), which is the canonical EKS
# worker-SG shape: workers must reach AWS APIs, ECR, image registries, and
# the public internet (for OS / chart pulls) over NAT.
#
# Tightening egress would require interface VPC endpoints for ECR-API,
# ECR-DKR, STS, Secrets Manager, EC2, autoscaling, EKS — deferred per
# docs/eks-hardening.md follow-up #11 (pay endpoints when NAT bill warrants).
# Reconsider this entry once those endpoints are wired.
AWS-0104

# AWS-0040 — Public cluster access is enabled.
# We deliberately enable `endpoint_public_access = true` on the EKS control
# plane, but **gated by `endpoint_public_access_cidrs = var.api_public_access_cidrs`**
# (validation rejects empty list and 0.0.0.0/0 — see variables.tf). This is
# docs/eks-hardening.md item #2: not fully private, but allowlisted, so
# operators can `kubectl` from Percona office / VPN egress without a bastion.
#
# Going fully private (endpoint_public_access = false) would require a VPN
# tunnel or bastion host inside the VPC for every operator session. Out of
# scope for v1; revisit when the operator workflow can absorb that cost.
AWS-0040
